data-triple-N3.o: "Emeritus is a Latin past participle that means "having served one's time" or "having merited one's discharge by service" (Latin e-, "out", and meritus, "merited"). In current usage, it is a postpositive adjective used to designate a retired professor, bishop, president, prime minister, or other professional; as such it refers to the post-retirement status of at least one pope."@en
